website_content.content:
Watch Jon Stewart and Anne Hathaway Totally Lose It After She Describes the Plot of Her Latest Movie
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
**Anne Hathaway’s** interview on _The Daily Show_ last night started innocently enough. **Jon Stewart** cracked a few jokes about  and her band Rilo Kiley. Hathaway gently mocked her own singing in her latest film, . But then the evening took a sharp turn. When Hathaway finished describing the plot of her latest film, she and Stewart both dissolved into uncontrollable laughter. In their defense, the plot description starts with a Ph.D. student in Morocco and ends with a teenager in a coma. Sometimes all you can do is laugh.
Watching it again, it looks like there _might_ be an edit between the end of Hathaway’s description and when Stewart loses it. (There’s a more obvious edit later in the segment.) But not knowing whether we’re in on the whole joke doesn’t make the derailing of this interview (the giggles continue throughout) any less enjoyable.

Anne Hathaway Can’t Stop Laughing About How Serious Her New Movie Is; Charms Jon Stewart, the World
===================================================================================================
]
By , a Vulture writer and host of Good One: A Podcast About Jokes
Last night on _The Daily Show_, Anne Hathaway and Jon Stewart got a true case of the giggles. You’ve been there: _Something_ happens, and for some reason, it is the funniest possible thing, so you laugh, and then the fact that you laugh makes you laugh more, and you literally cannot stop yourself. In this case, it was all set off by how incredibly serious Hathaway’s new movie, _Song One_, sounds, and how casually she describes the plot to Jon. This proves that anything can be funny if you say it over and over again, even if it’s describing your brother getting into a car accident and falling into a coma.

A video of actor Anne Hathaway laughing at an inappropriate joke is doing its rounds online. In the viral clip, Hathaway was seen talking to American TV host Jon Stewart and she asks him the double entendre joke and then gives the answer herself. However, the clip that is garnering massive attention online is a deepfake video and was created by the use of Artificial Technology.
The viral clip of Hathaway cracking the joke has made several people believe that she did in fact crack the joke on The Daily Show. The video is currently being circulated on social media platforms like Youtube, Instagram, and TikTok and it has managed to amass millions of views.
!
For those unaware the viral clip, which is being used as a deepfake, of Anne Hathaway laughing with host Jon Stewart is from her visit to the show back in 2015.
* * *
Anne Hathaway 6.9 joke video is not real and was created by the use of AI
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
As internet users came across the viral clip of Anne Hathaway cracking the joke, they started sharing hilarious reactions and fell for the fake video too. However, according to _HITC_, this viral clip was created using advanced AI technology in which they copied Hathaway's voice and edited her face to make it seem as if the video is real.

It is worth noting that this deepfake video used a clip from 2015 when Anne appeared on The Daily Show. During the show, she was talking about her then-latest movie, _Song One_, and laughed about it.
!

> “And then her little brother who’s 19 calls her up and says ‘I’m dropping out of college’ to become a musician. And she doesn’t react very well and they haven’t spoken for six months and then he gets hit by a car and is in a coma.”

**Anne Hathaway**'s new movie, _Song One_, is a romantic drama that will probably have more than a few tear-jerking moments, but when the actress stopped by _The_ _Daily Show_ Wednesday, she and **Jon Stewart** couldn't help but laugh about it.
Their interview started as normal as ever, with Stewart making a few quips about the music in the movie and Hathaway's friend **Jenny Lewis** and her band **Rilo Kiley**, but when the _Les Misérables_ star described the plot of new independent film, uncontrollable laughter ensued.
It looks like there might be a _slight_ edit to the clip, as if we're missing some part of the joke that would cause them to laugh so hard. But in her defense, she did describe it in such a way that began with a PhD student and ended with a boy in a coma, and it did sound a _little_ silly. While she definitely didn't mean for it to come out that way, both of them couldn't control themselves.
!Comedy Central
"Your brother's in a coma, that is true," Stewart said while tearing up from laughing so hard. "I've seen it and that was still a bit of a spoiler alert. I'm sorry."
Practically in tears, Hathaway recalled that a journalist told her that while he was watching the coma scene, he fell off his treadmill! Of course, the talk show host couldn't pass up the opportunity to mock himself when she said that.
"Here's the only difference between me and that guy," he said. "I don't use the treadmill! I did fall off there, but I do not use it."
